HEADWORD: Graciously
<hw>Gra"cious*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In
a gracious manner; courteously; benignantly.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fortunately; luckily.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
